Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.48,0:00:17.62,Song,,0,0,0,,'Mid pleasures and palaces though we may roam {the song is a Japanese version of https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Home!_Sweet_Home! so I've decided to go with the original english text for clarity; japanese lyrics: 埴生の宿も わが宿\N玉の装い 羨まじ\Nのどかなりや 春の空\N花はあるじ 鳥は友\Nおお わが宿よ\N楽しとも たのもしや ; also the first line is this episode's title}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.62,0:00:28.75,Song,,0,0,0,,Be it ever so humble, there's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.75,0:00:39.76,Song,,0,0,0,,A charm from the skies seems to hallow us there
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.76,0:00:51.36,Song,,0,0,0,,Which, seek thro' the world, is ne'er met elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:01:02.08,Song,,0,0,0,,Home, home, sweet, sweet home
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.08,0:01:11.55,Song,,0,0,0,,There's no place like home
Dialogue: 10,0:00:16.57,0:00:22.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The war left us all with tragic memories.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:23.37,0:00:30.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This is the true story of one battalion in the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:48.40,0:00:51.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,The situation on the battlefield turned against us.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:51.36,0:00:55.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,Everywhere, the British and Indian armies pushed us back.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:55.32,0:00:59.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,We moved camp every day,\N from mountain to mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.08,0:01:00.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,We had to cross the border
Dialogue: 10,0:01:00.79,0:01:04.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,into Thailand, still nominally\N an independent nation, when required.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:06.79,0:01:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure the ammunition is tied down!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:11.55,0:01:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the enemy!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.38,0:01:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Scatter! Get down!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.64,0:01:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Retreat, everyone! \NTake cover behind the rocks!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.66,0:01:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.91,0:01:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, men!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.86,0:01:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.93,0:01:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.85,0:02:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We should sing.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.23,0:02:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Times like this are what a choir is for, to cheer us up!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.27,0:02:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima, would you play your harp?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:26.58,Song,,0,0,0,,{Ryoshuu / 旅愁 - a folk song; full lyrics: ふけゆく秋の夜　旅の空の\Nわびしき思いに　ひとり悩む\N恋しやふるさと　なつかし父母\N夢路にたどるは　さとの家路\Nふけゆく秋の夜　旅の空の\Nわびしき思いに　ひとり悩む\N\N窓うつ嵐に　夢もやぶれ\Nはるけきかなたに　心まよう\N恋しやふるさと　なつかし父母\N思いに浮かぶは　杜（もり）のこずえ\N窓うつ嵐に　夢もやぶれ\Nはるけきかなたに　心まよう; translation from https://douyo-shouka.com/ryoshu/}On a drowsy autumn night
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.58,0:02:31.25,Song,,0,0,0,,Under the sky of travel
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.92,0:02:41.89,Song,,0,0,0,,I am alone with a lonely thought
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:48.56,Song,,0,0,0,,I miss my hometown
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:54.27,Song,,0,0,0,,And my remembered father and mother
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:59.70,Song,,0,0,0,,In my dreams, I am following
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:05.37,Song,,0,0,0,,The way home to my hometown
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:16.30,Song,,0,0,0,,My dream was shattered by the window storm
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:26.47,Song,,0,0,0,,My heart is lost far away
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.32,0:02:59.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,We sang pretty well, really.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.70,0:03:02.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was a music student before the war,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.74,0:03:05.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,so I taught the troops how to sing.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.37,0:03:09.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,The enemy could find us at any moment, and we'd be killed the next minute.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.91,0:03:13.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,But until then, we at least tried to fill our hearts with song.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.63,0:03:16.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's what I'd hoped for\N when I started the choir.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.47,0:03:23.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,Private Mizushima was an expert\N on the Burmese harp.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.30,0:03:26.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,He hadn't played anything before coming to Thailand,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.47,0:03:30.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,but whether or not it was innate talent, \Nhe improved remarkably fast
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.02,0:03:34.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,and soon began devising and playing splendid accompaniments himself.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.70,0:03:48.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,The main problem for us was food.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.70,0:03:52.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,The enemy was always lying in ambush, one village ahead of us.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.83,0:03:54.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,We couldn't let our guard down.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.92,0:03:59.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,Then, one day, we spotted a village below a cliff.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.52,0:04:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.02,0:04:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The village is safe. Let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.44,0:04:21.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was a fantastic welcome.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.90,0:04:24.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,They held a feast \Nand even brought out wine.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.86,0:04:30.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Burmese are devoted Buddhists and are strictly forbidden to drink.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.50,0:04:35.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,But the villagers somehow managed to get this wine just for us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.42,0:04:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}We're deeply touched by this unexpected welcome,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.34,0:04:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}so we'll sing a song in gratitude. {思わぬ歓迎をうけて、心より感謝しますお礼に歌をうたいます}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.39,0:04:59.23,Song,,0,0,0,,{荒城の月 / koujonotsuki - another folk song; full lyrics: 春 高楼の花の宴\Nめぐる盃 かげさして\N千代の松が枝 わけ出でし\Nむかしの光 いまいずこ\N秋 陣営の 霜の色\N鳴きゆく雁の数見せて\N植うる剣に照りそいし\Nむかしの光 いまいずこ\N今 荒城の 夜半の月\Nかわらぬ光 誰がためぞ\N垣に残るはただかつら\N松にうたうはただ嵐\N天上影は変らねど\N栄枯は移る 世のすがた\N写さんとてか 今もなお\Nああ荒城の 夜半の月; translation from https://douyo-shouka.com/koujyou-no-tsuki/}In spring, a cherry blossom viewing party is held in the high tower
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.23,0:05:11.37,Song,,0,0,0,,The moon’s shadow shines\N on the cups we exchange
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.87,0:05:24.47,Song,,0,0,0,,Shining through pine tree branches\N that have lasted for a thousand years
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.47,0:05:38.98,Song,,0,0,0,,Where is the glory of the past?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.44,0:05:46.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,That prompted the Burmese to start singing as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.99,0:05:50.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,The feast turned into a lively party, \Nalmost like one in the city. {not sure what they meant by 演芸会}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.38,0:06:06.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,We had such a good time\N that it took us a while to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.59,0:06:11.05,Song,,0,0,0,,{the song is "Mugi to heitai / 麦と兵隊" - another folk song; full lyrics: 徐州(じょしゅう)々々と　人馬(じんば)は進む\N徐州居よいか　住みよいか\N酒落(しゃれ)た文句に　振り返えりゃ; translation from https://lyricstranslate.com/en/mugi-heitai-wheat-and-soldier.html}To Xuzhou, Xuzhou, both man and horse advance
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:16.56,Song,,0,0,0,,Is Xuzhou a good place to stay, \Na good place to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:21.48,Song,,0,0,0,,Turning back at the humorous lyrics...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.22,0:06:11.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,Before we knew it, \Nall the Burmese had vanished.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.40,0:06:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stop singing!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.32,0:06:23.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,We suddenly became nervous.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.86,0:06:26.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,It wasn't uncommon for villagers
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.90,0:06:29.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,to welcome us warmly and warn the enemy at the same time.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.78,0:06:31.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,The situation was reversed.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.16,0:06:33.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,We had to prepare for a battle immediately.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.41,0:06:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't move. Keep singing.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.08,0:06:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy in the jungle may have\N surrounded this assembly hall.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.42,0:06:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't let them know\N that we've figured it out now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.51,0:06:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep singing while we prepare.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.68,0:06:55.35,Song,,0,0,0,,{dormitory/folk song "ああ玉杯に花うけて(一高寮歌)"; full lyrics: 嗚呼玉杯(ぎょくはい)に花うけて\N緑酒(りょくしゅ)に月の影やどし\N治安の夢に耽(ふけ)りたる\N栄華(えいが)の巷低く見て\N向ヶ岡にそそり立つ\N五寮の健児意気高し; translation from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P3e_-r5geiM}They're receiving flowers in their beautiful cups
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.35,0:06:59.85,Song,,0,0,0,,Reflecting the shadow of the moon \Nin their delicious sake
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.85,0:07:04.44,Song,,0,0,0,,And indulging in dreams of security
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.44,0:07:09.07,Song,,0,0,0,,While looking down on such a prosperous society
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.07,0:07:18.62,Song,,0,0,0,,The youth of the five dormitories\N rising in Mukogaoka are in high spirits
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.54,0:07:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy appears to be \Na substantial force.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.54,0:07:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know when they'll open fire all at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.05,0:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be dark soon. \NWe need to buy time until then.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.30,0:07:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep clapping your hands, laughing, and singing.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.93,0:07:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, our ammunition \Nis still out in the open.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.89,0:07:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's hit by enemy fire, it's all over.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.14,0:07:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to find a way to get that inside.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.96,0:08:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Once more!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.96,0:08:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:34.20,Song,,0,0,0,,'Mid pleasures and palaces though we may roam {same as the first song of the episode; 埴生の宿も わが宿\N玉の装い 羨まじ\Nのどかなりや 春の空\N花はあるじ 鳥は友\Nおお わが宿よ\N楽しとも たのもしや; translation from https://www.mu-tech.org/ScoreImageSSL/Lyric_HanyuNoYado.html }
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:45.12,Song,,0,0,0,,Be it ever so humble, there's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:55.63,Song,,0,0,0,,A charm from the skies seems to hallow us there
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.63,0:09:06.81,Song,,0,0,0,,Which, seek thro' the world, is ne'er met elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.81,0:09:16.53,Song,,0,0,0,,Home, home, sweet, sweet home...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.53,0:09:18.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,Night came quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.99,0:09:21.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,In the tropics, the boundary between day and night is distinct,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.95,0:09:24.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,and once the sun sets, \Nit turns pitch black in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:46.64,Song,,0,0,0,,...though we may roam {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Home!_Sweet_Home! - I guess that answers where that other translation for the japanese version came from}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:57.82,Song,,0,0,0,,Be it ever so humble, there's no place like home
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:10:09.33,Song,,0,0,0,,A charm from the skies seems to hallow us there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:20.26,Song,,0,0,0,,Which, seek thro' the world, is ne'er met elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.26,0:10:25.52,Song,,0,0,0,,If a body meet a body,\Ncomin' thro the rye {https://hymnary.org/text/if_a_body_meet_a_body_comin_thro_the_rye}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:30.77,Song,,0,0,0,,If a body kiss a body,\Nneed a body cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.77,0:10:35.94,Song,,0,0,0,,Ev'ry lassie has her laddie,\Nnane, they say, ha'e I
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:41.74,Song,,0,0,0,,Yet a' the lads they smile on me,\Nwhen comin' thro' the rye
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:47.04,Song,,0,0,0,,{故郷の空 / Kokyou no sora - a folk song, borrowing the melody from "thro the rye"; full lyrics: 夕空はれて　あきかぜふき\Nつきかげ落ちて　鈴虫なく\Nおもえば遠し　故郷のそら\Nああ　わが父母　いかにおわす\N\Nすみゆく水に　秋萩たれ\N玉なす露は　すすきにみつ\Nおもえば似たり　故郷の野辺\Nああ　わが兄弟(はらから) たれと遊ぶ; translation from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GE_Z2BnIhsE (OMG a version by Chieko Baisho o (≧∇≦o))}The evening sky clears and the autumn wind blows
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:52.04,Song,,0,0,0,,Moonlight fills the sky, \Na bell cricket chirps
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.04,0:10:57.01,Song,,0,0,0,,I think of the sky of my hometown, so far away
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.01,0:11:02.93,Song,,0,0,0,,Oh, I wonder how my parents live
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:07.93,Song,,0,0,0,,{restarted from the beginning; if you hate this, remove the thro the rye lyrics from here on, or just remove both since it's the repetition of earlier anyway}The evening sky clears and the autumn wind blows\N{\3c&HC22E22&}If a body meet a body, comin' thro the rye
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.93,0:11:13.11,Song,,0,0,0,,Moonlight fills the sky, a bell cricket chirps\N{\3c&HC22E22&}If a body kiss a body, need a body cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:17.78,Song,,0,0,0,,I think of the sky of my hometown, so far away \N{\3c&HC22E22&}Ev'ry lassie has her laddie, nane, they say, ha'e I
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:24.12,Song,,0,0,0,,Oh, I wonder how my old parents live\N{\3c&HC22E22& }Yet a' the lads they smile on me, comin' thro' the rye
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.81,0:11:16.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,That night, they told us the war had been over for three days.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.78,0:11:19.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,That night, we threw down our weapons.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.75,0:11:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We've surrendered. Japan has surrendered.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.84,0:11:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to feel about this yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.18,0:11:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And as for our future...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.18,0:11:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't yet know where they'll take us, \Nor what they'll make us do,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.68,0:11:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or even whether we'll live or die.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.77,0:11:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've been through life and death together all this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.56,0:11:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll face the fate coming to us together as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.90,0:12:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We may end up buried here in Burma,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.95,0:12:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but even then, we'll go as a single unit.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.24,0:12:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're lucky and we get\N to go home one day,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.29,0:12:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we won't leave a single man behind.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.33,0:12:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go home together \Nto rebuild our homeland.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.75,0:12:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I have to say for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.80,0:12:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they're planning to move us \Nto the POW camp in Mudon soon. {https://maps.app.goo.gl/zXGeJyeZps3Xj7A88}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.98,0:12:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.56,0:12:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When they lock us all up in the camp, \Nthey might just execute us then.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.48,0:12:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.15,0:12:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Mudon, anyway?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.24,0:12:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.45,0:12:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima! Where's Mizushima?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.91,0:12:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.62,0:12:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just received a report.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.13,0:12:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A Japanese unit is holed up\N in the mountains over there
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.92,0:13:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and won't surrender, no matter what.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.38,0:13:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Three days ago,\N the British launched an attack,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.22,0:13:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but they still couldn't smoke them out. {/the fighting continues}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.80,0:13:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If this continues, the unit will be completely destroyed.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.22,0:13:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked the British commander\N to take one of us to the mountain,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.52,0:13:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can explain things and prevent unnecessary casualties.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.03,0:13:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, Mizushima? \NWill you go?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.07,0:13:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you won't, I will.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.99,0:13:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.75,0:13:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to know. {lit: so you will go, huh?}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.83,0:13:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure how I can explain it to them,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.75,0:13:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but if I speak to them directly, \NI'm sure they'll understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.25,0:13:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They're transferring our unit south soon, to Mudon.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.55,0:13:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,After you've done your part, \Nbe sure to come there too.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.01,0:13:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I talked this over with a British officer,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.81,0:13:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so he promised to send you there personally. {lit: responsibly send you there}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.14,0:13:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.31,0:13:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I'm done, \NI'll be joining you in Mudon.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.40,0:14:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.45,0:14:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.41,0:14:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.13,0:14:27.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,Soon, the British moved our unit
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.17,0:14:29.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,out of the mountains.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.18,0:14:33.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,We crossed the Sittang River and headed down to Mudon.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.19,0:14:51.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,For a long time, many years on end,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.16,0:14:55.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,we had hardly ever spent such quiet days.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.29,0:14:59.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,The days spent consumed by battle,\N constantly hounded by tension and anxiety,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.54,0:15:03.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,now felt like a distant fairy tale.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.04,0:15:08.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,In any case, as we waited\N for the day we'd return home,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.05,0:15:11.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,many peaceful, quiet days passed.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.55,0:15:16.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,But gradually, an uneasy feeling \Nbegan to stir among us.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.01,0:15:21.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,Although many days had passed, \NMizushima still hadn't returned.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.23,0:15:25.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,We began to wonder \Nwhat had happened to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.75,0:15:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where Mizushima is.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.18,0:15:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been here a month,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.84,0:15:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and we haven't heard a thing. \NIt ain't right!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.43,0:15:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's dead already.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.73,0:16:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't talk nonsense!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.39,0:16:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Misushima's too smart\N to get himself killed!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.06,0:16:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But I hear fighting continues in that village on Triangle Mountain,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.24,0:16:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so even if he didn't die, he might be injured and lying in some hospital.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.45,0:16:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be good, but I wonder if there's any way we could know for sure?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.37,0:16:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have gone myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.46,0:16:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I figured Mizushima would be more convincing,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.50,0:16:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so I asked him to go talk to them.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.63,0:16:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I realize that\Nit was {\i1}my{\i0} responsibility.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.60,0:16:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Captain.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.14,0:16:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizushima will be back, sooner or later.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.56,0:16:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably put on a loincloth \Nand went native.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.31,0:16:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll bet he's receiving a warm welcome in every nearby village.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.03,0:16:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll just stroll in later, saying, "Sorry I'm late!"\N Cheerful, like nothing happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.03,0:16:59.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,Another month thus passed,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.37,0:17:03.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,but there was no still sign of Mizushima.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.79,0:17:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{doesn't sound like indian or anything else from the region, I'd bet they couldn't find a burmese translator at hand and were just winging it, as this sounds like Japanese intentionally made to sound foreign, but it's still japanese}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.21,0:17:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.38,0:17:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.38,0:17:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.68,0:17:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Granny! Good to see you!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.18,0:17:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been waiting!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.47,0:17:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That bonehead Indian soldier!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.14,0:17:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked if I had a permit with me. {permit; license; licence}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.89,0:17:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a new one\N who doesn't know me yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.07,0:17:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Granny, would you give me \Na banana for my shirt?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.07,0:17:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.36,0:17:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how about some chambakka for this broom? {??? this chandaka is not in any japanese dictionary so can't know for sure}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.20,0:17:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it from Yashi leaves.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.37,0:17:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good workmanship. \NOkay, it's a deal.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.75,0:17:48.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,This old lady has been doing business with Japanese soldiers
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.42,0:17:53.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,from when the Japanese army was still in power and stationed in this town.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.13,0:17:54.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,A huge Japanophile,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.67,0:17:57.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,she’d picked up the language\N from the occupying Kansai unit, {I assume they mean the garrison of that town was from kansai}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:57.88,0:18:00.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,and now spoke with a thick Kansai accent herself.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.10,0:18:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, did you look into \Nwhat I asked before?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.47,0:18:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you want again?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.60,0:18:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.65,0:18:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the soldier that was sent to Triangle Mountain!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.32,0:18:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Is it true that the wounded soldiers\N being treated at the hospital in this town
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.78,0:18:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,were really captured at Triangle Mountain?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.16,0:18:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, is there a Japanese soldier \Nfrom a different battalion
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.54,0:18:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,who was sent to negotiate with them?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.87,0:18:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happened to him?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.17,0:18:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I need to know.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.25,0:18:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure to ask around\N in that hospital
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.84,0:18:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,if I happen to pass by \Nin the next few days.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.01,0:18:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do, we'll repay you\N in any way we can.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.05,0:18:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget this time!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:42.30,0:18:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.14,0:18:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you don't forget again!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.10,0:18:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it, don't worry. \NThanks for your things.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.93,0:18:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye now. Goodbye!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.98,0:18:55.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,A few days later, she told us what she'd learned.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.15,0:19:00.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was news that plunged us \Ninto even deeper despair.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.16,0:19:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The soldiers at that hospital
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.53,0:19:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,were definitely stationed somewhere called Triangle Mountain,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.79,0:19:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or something like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.46,0:19:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And they remembered the man from another battalion
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.63,0:19:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you were asking about.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:13.54,0:19:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to him, they stopped fighting before it was too late,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.96,0:19:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and their lives were spared.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.68,0:19:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But they don't know\N what happened to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.89,0:19:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They said he was running across\N the battlefield through a hail of bullets,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.72,0:19:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so he probably got killed.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.19,0:19:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He died in battle?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.78,0:19:48.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,But several days later, at sunset, we saw something strange.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.95,0:19:53.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,We were on our way back from repairing a bridge outside the village...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.98,0:20:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.89,0:21:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He's so incredibly like him!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.18,0:21:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks just like Mizushima!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.69,0:21:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's call him by name!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.81,0:21:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you fool!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.44,0:21:42.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,After working all day,\N everyone fell asleep instantly.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.32,0:21:45.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't sleep that night.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.40,0:21:49.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,That Burmese monk reminded me\N of Mizushima too much.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.28,0:21:55.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,But why would Mizushima come to see us dressed up like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.71,0:21:58.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,And if that Burmese monk {\i0}was{\i1} Mizushima,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.50,0:22:01.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,why did he just rush by without speaking?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.38,0:22:03.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,It must have been someone else.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.01,0:22:08.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,"We know... that Mizushima is dead."
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.97,0:22:11.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's what I kept telling myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.53,0:22:37.41,Song,,0,0,0,,I write a letter to my loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.12,0:22:44.34,Song,,0,0,0,,I write and tear it, tear it, and write again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.34,0:22:50.89,Song,,0,0,0,,I throw the rolled up paper at the window
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.89,0:22:58.06,Song,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside, just like the tears on my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.14,0:23:05.94,Song,,0,0,0,,Life is a sea, youth is a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.94,0:23:12.99,Song,,0,0,0,,My love, please come and save me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.99,0:23:15.41,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.29,0:23:18.54,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:26.67,Song,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.67,0:23:36.10,Song,,0,0,0,,Not a single star in sight, in the sea of ​​sadness
